لِصّ(لُصوص) : thief/robber : 13

سَرِقَة(سَرِقات) : theft/robbery : 13

تحْقيق(تَحْقيقات) : investigation : 13

خِطاب(خِطابات) : letter, address, speech : 13 : From خَاطَبَ • (ḵāṭaba) III, non-past يُخَاطِبُ‎ (yuḵāṭibu) 1. to address. Same root as khutbah خُطْبَة‎ Friday sermon. Note different root from كَتَبَ "to write"

مَكْتُوب(مَكَاتِيب) : letter, message, something written, destiny : 13+ : Example of a word for "letter" with k-t-b root, to contrast with خِطاب

قَصْر(قُصور) : palace : 13 : Also "large stone building, castle, fortress". From Latin castrum. Compare Classical Syriac ܩܰܨܪܳܐ‎ (“qaṣrā”), Hebrew קְצָרָה‎ (qəṣārâ). Cognate with English "castle"

فِنْجان(فَناجين) : cup : 13 : From Persian پنگان‎ (pengân).

